Exploratory Analysis

MISSING MIGRANTS

The initial dataset contains 4286 data items and the following data attributes.

  • region The region in which the incident took place
  • date Estimated date of death
  • year The year in which the incident occurred
  • deaths The sum of the number of dead and missing
  • women The number of females found dead or missing. If unknown, it is left blank.
  • men The number of males found dead or missing. If unknown, it is left blank.
  • children The number of individuals under the age of 18 found dead or missing. If unknown, it is left blank.
  • survivors The number of migrants that survived the incident, if known
  • cause_of_death The determination of conditions resulting in the migrant’s death
  • location_description Place where the death(s) occurred or where the body or bodies were found
  • location_coordinates Place where the death(s) occurred or where the body or bodies were found
  • url Articles that reported the incident

One of the dimensions I intend to investigate is the information richness. So I need a dataset with as much complete data as possible. The first decision is considering only the rows that contain the number of dead women and children.

The resulting dataset contains 103 now.
